            <h3 class="display-4">Description</h3>
                <p style="margin-left: 350px; margin-right: 350px;">
                For the project, we decide to create a Node.js backend instead of PHP since we are more familiar with
                this technology.
                As a result, Heroku is our cloud provider as we consider it is easier to work with a Node.js project on
                Heroku.
                Besides, Heroku provide a free tier, so the server can stay online almost 24/7
                (It goes to sleep if the server is idle for a while, then awake when a request is retrieved).
                <br>
                <br>
                In summary, the main technologies that we use for our project are Heroku cloud, Node.js backend, Express
                framework, and PostgreSQL DBMS.
                Unlike what we did in the previous assignment, our code is edited using VS Code and tested on local
                machine by deploying a local Node.js/PostgreSQL server.
                Then the code base is pushed to our GitHub repository and automatically deployed to Heroku cloud.
                </p>
